BIODUN Stephen’s new flick, Strangers, will premiere today, April 29, 2022, at the Genesis Cinemas, Maryland Mall, Lagos. Directed by Stephens, the film is in collaboration with Banji Adesanmi’s Inspaya TV. Speaking at a press screening, Adesanmi revealed that Strangers has already won the Gold award for Directing at International Independent Film Awards held in Los Angeles.   Bob-Manuel Udokwu: Fame once got me upgraded seat on…     ‘Ushers are not prostitutes’     Bouqui: Nothing affects one’s destiny like sex   Adjudged a story of resilience, hope, and heroism, the first-person narrative tells an emotional and inspirational story excellently rendered by a selection of actors that include Lateef Adedimeji, Bimbo Oshin, Bolaji Ogunmola, Debbie Felix, Femi Adebayo, Ndamo Damarise, Chris Iheuwa, Jide Kosoko, Bimbo Akintola, Mide Glover and Nonso Odogwu. ‘Strangers’ follows the life of a remote village boy, untamed by civilization, but hit by calamitous events that changed the course of his existence. Banji Adesanmi, the Executive Producer of the movie said he was inspired to put the story into play because of the resilience of the characters involved in the true-life events. “Strangers chronicles a series of despairing events with miraculous outcomes. It is a story that is sweet to hear, I decided to adapt it into a screenplay and joined forces with notable figures that can translate it into a captivating motion picture. The international recognition for the movie is a testament to this,” he said.